Ali Al Balawi, an 83-year-old Saudi man who has 126 children and grandchildren, has remarried for the 11th time in Tabuk, north-western Saudi Arabia. Al Balawi, who has 18 sons, 20 daughters and 88 grandsons and daughters, celebrated his 11th marriage with a wedding reception in the presence of his family members and friends. Saudi Arabia marriage law to bend for Ronaldo, lover Naira Scarcity: Police beef up security around banks in Bayelsa With the new bride, Al Balawi has four wives now. He says he is healthy and has never suffered from any illness. “So, there is nothing can prevent him from remarrying,” he said. “I have financial, mental and physical capacity to maintain four wives,” Al Balawi said.